about.summary: Fit smoothing-splines mixed-effects models to replicated functional data sets and visualise the results.

name: r-sme
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.0.2' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-sme
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/sme_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/sme/sme_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: e62e0f7c1eeaa49dd7b2fc50a633e3e590a5743aeac7a1eff51a8bae83bf5f3f

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 2
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-lattice
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-lattice

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('sme')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('sme')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/mberk/sme
  license: GPL (>= 3)
  summary: Fit smoothing-splines mixed-effects models to replicated functional data sets and
    visualise the results.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - MathiasHaudgaard
    - FrodePedersen
    - ArneKr
